name: performance-engineering
description: Systematic performance optimization for mobile apps - profiling, bottleneck identification, and measurable improvements

# Purpose
Find and fix performance problems through measurement, not guessing. Optimize what matters: startup time, frame rate, battery, memory, and network efficiency.

# When to use
Use this skill when:
- App feels slow or janky
- Users report performance issues
- Battery drain complaints
- Memory warnings or crashes
- Before/after major features
- Optimizing critical user journeys

# Inputs
- Symptom description (slow screen, jank, battery drain, etc.)
- Device constraints (low-end targets?)
- Current measurements if available
- Code/screens involved

# Output Format (required)
1) Performance budget (targets)
2) Measurement plan (what/how to measure)
3) Bottleneck hypothesis (ranked)
4) Profiling results analysis
5) Optimization plan (ordered by impact/effort)
6) Verification (before/after metrics)

# Performance Budgets (Mobile)

## Startup Time
- Cold start: < 2s to interactive
- Warm start: < 500ms
- Measure: time from launch to first meaningful paint

## Frame Rate
- Target: 60fps (16.6ms per frame)
- Acceptable: no frames > 32ms (drops below 30fps)
- Jank budget: < 1% of frames dropped

## Memory
- Baseline: < 150MB for typical app
- Peak: < 300MB during heavy operations
- No unbounded growth (leaks)

## Battery
- Background: minimal wake-ups, no polling
- Foreground: efficient network batching
- Location: use significant-change only when possible

## Network
- API calls: < 500ms p95
- Payload size: compress, paginate
- Offline-first where possible

# Profiling Methodology

## Step 1: Reproduce with measurement
- Use release/profile builds (debug hides real perf)
- Profile on target devices (not just simulator)
- Capture baseline metrics first

## Step 2: Identify the bottleneck type
| Symptom | Likely Bottleneck | Tool |
|---------|-------------------|------|
| Slow startup | Heavy init, sync I/O | Timeline, startup trace |
| Jank/stutter | Main thread blocking | Frame timeline |
| High memory | Leaks, large objects | Memory profiler |
| Battery drain | Wake locks, polling | Battery profiler |
| Slow screens | Expensive builds, N+1 | Network + timeline |

## Step 3: Drill down
- CPU: Which functions take time? Sampling profiler
- Memory: What objects are retained? Heap snapshot
- I/O: What's blocking? Async timeline
- Network: What requests are slow? Network profiler

## Step 4: Fix and verify
- Change ONE thing at a time
- Re-measure with same conditions
- Document the improvement (before/after)

# Common Bottlenecks & Fixes

## Startup
| Problem | Fix |
|---------|-----|
| Heavy initialization | Defer non-critical init, lazy load |
| Sync network on start | Async + cached fallback |
| Large asset loading | Lazy load, compress, cache |
| Too many providers/services | Initialize on-demand |

## UI/Rendering (Flutter-specific)
| Problem | Fix |
|---------|-----|
| Expensive build() | Extract widgets, use const |
| Rebuilding entire tree | Targeted rebuilds, selectors |
| Large lists | ListView.builder, pagination |
| Image jank | Cached images, sized placeholders |
| Complex animations | RepaintBoundary, simpler curves |
| Shader compilation jank | Warm up shaders, simplify effects |

## Memory
| Problem | Fix |
|---------|-----|
| Image caching unbounded | LRU cache with size limit |
| Listeners not disposed | Proper dispose() in StatefulWidget |
| Large objects in memory | Stream/chunk processing |
| Retained references | Weak references, proper cleanup |

## Network/Database
| Problem | Fix |
|---------|-----|
| N+1 queries | Batch fetching, joins |
| No pagination | Cursor/offset pagination |
| Repeated identical requests | Request deduplication, caching |
| Large payloads | Compression, partial responses |
| Slow queries | Indexes, query optimization |

## Battery
| Problem | Fix |
|---------|-----|
| Polling | Push notifications, realtime subscriptions |
| Frequent location updates | Significant-change monitoring |
| Background work | Batch, defer to charging |
| Wake locks held | Release promptly |

# Supabase-Specific Performance

## Query Optimization
- Use select() to fetch only needed columns
- Add .limit() to all list queries
- Use range queries for pagination
- Leverage Supabase's built-in caching headers

## Realtime Efficiency
- Subscribe to specific rows, not entire tables
- Use filters in subscriptions
- Unsubscribe when not needed
- Batch updates on client side

## Edge Functions
- Keep cold start minimal (small bundles)
- Cache expensive computations
- Use connection pooling for DB

# Measurement Tools

## Flutter
- DevTools Performance tab
- DevTools Memory tab
- flutter run --profile
- Timeline events API

## Mobile Platform
- Xcode Instruments (iOS)
- Android Studio Profiler
- Firebase Performance Monitoring

## Custom Metrics
- Add timing logs around critical paths
- Track custom events (startup phases, screen loads)
- Monitor in production (percentiles, not averages)

# Anti-Patterns (avoid)
- Optimizing without measuring first
- Optimizing on debug builds
- Testing only on high-end devices
- Using averages instead of percentiles
- Premature optimization of cold paths
- Adding complexity for marginal gains

# Optimization Priority Matrix

| Impact | Effort | Action |
|--------|--------|--------|
| High | Low | Do immediately |
| High | High | Plan carefully |
| Low | Low | Quick wins if time permits |
| Low | High | Skip unless critical |

# Verification Checklist
- [ ] Measured on real device (not simulator)
- [ ] Used release/profile build
- [ ] Baseline captured before changes
- [ ] Improvement measured (percentage)
- [ ] No regression in other metrics
- [ ] Tested on low-end device target
